The paper discusses the problem of exploring and analyzing the Web to discover security-relevant information, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The proposed approach involves collecting and integrating textual, relational, and temporal data, which suggests the use of information retrieval (cs.IR), social network analysis (cs.SI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and data mining (cs.CY) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR, followed by cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CL, and cs.CY.
